---
description: Runway Picker shared coding standards
alwaysApply: true
---

Use `AGENTS.md` in the repository root as the canonical instruction source.

Required repository standards:
- Preserve separation of concerns across `src/domain`, `src/application`, `src/services`, and `src/ui`.
- Keep strict TypeScript contracts and avoid untyped interfaces at boundaries.
- Maintain test coverage and quality gates (`typecheck`, `lint`, `test:coverage`, `build`, `lint:workflows`).
- Follow Conventional Commits for PR titles and squash merge outcomes.
- Keep release/deploy changes compatible with automated GitHub Releases and release-triggered production deploys.
